{
  "stem": "1415.4",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, like I said, you know-- I have to qualify that, that we did arrive to Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We considered it Auschwitz everywhere, but this was Birkenau.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it was B lager, and it was Block 16.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I was-- there were a lot of people in there, and when we arrived, and the people from our camp asked me to sing, I felt obliged.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because I figure, these people that were next to me, there was on one side-- and I think I probably went over more than one person, must have continued on.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And if they asked me to sing, I better oblige them and sing to make up for what I did to them every night, practically.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Because all they were giving us is water and-- and just, they called it soup.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And that night, they give us, like, coffee, they called it, which was like mud.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so, I felt obliged to sing.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So I got up, and I sang That's the song I learned from that old man in Ostrowiec.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I sang it, and after it was through, I heard applause, and then suddenly stop, and it and got very quiet, and I turned around, and there was the head of my camp, my block.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "My block eldester, they used to call it, somebody that was in charge of your block.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "She was a Jewish young woman who came from Czechoslovakia, and had a big ego on her, because she's been there for a long time, and considered us as privileged, and she showed it to us, that we were privileged, at every appel.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "She would make sure that somebody got it good.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "She wasn't very kind, she wasn't-- she-- she wanted to show to the Germans that she has authority.",
      "word_count": 18
    }
  ],
